\begin_layout Subsection
Continuous data matrix (CDM)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
CDM file format is a tab delimited matrix of items (i.e.
 genes) and conditions.
 The numbers in each cell indicates the values that this item has in that
 condition.
 Empty values can be represented with the hyphen '-'.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is useful for representing matrices (i.e.
 expression data for a microarray).
\end_layout

