\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Gene matrix (GMX)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
GMX file format is a simple tab delimited file to provide gene sets.
 Each column describes a gene set, the first row indicates the name of the
 gene set and the second row the description (you can leave description
 empty), the rest of rows are used to enumerate the genes related to this
 gene set.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Usually this format is used for representing modules but can also be used
 to represent binary data matrices (i.e.
 when you have lists of differentially expressed gens for different conditions).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
