\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Two columns mapping (TCM)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
TCM file format is a simple tab delimited file to provide gene sets.
 It has two columns, the first column indicates the ID of gene or biological
 element and the second column the name of the module it belongs to.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Usually this format is used for representing modules but can also be used
 to represent binary data matrices (i.e.
 when you have lists of differentially expressed gens for different conditions).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This format uses more disk space than others so it is better to use some
 of GMX or GMT, but usually it is how you get data from Biomart so Gitools
 supports it too.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
